** Young Writers' Studio Thurber House
------------------------------------------------------------

June 17th and July dates...

Young Writers’ Studio is designed for rising 9-12 grade students who embrace writing beyond the classroom. Every other Tuesday from 6:00-8:00 p.m., facilitator and local writer, Robert Loss, presents a different writing topic to push each individual creatively. Writers are also encouraged to submit a piece of work to be discussed during the second half of the session. Each author receives feedback about everything from character development to grammar.

Event Website >> (http://www.thurberhouse.org/assets/files/YWS%202014%20Summer.pdf)

